The article discusses the importance of affordable and high-quality child care, especially for working parents. It highlights the challenges faced by parents during the pandemic, such as closed schools and limited child care options. The article also mentions the efforts made by the government, particularly through the American Rescue Plan, to support child care centers and providers. The author emphasizes the need for fundamental changes in child care and advocates for investments in universal preschool and lowering costs for families. The article concludes by introducing the Secretary of Health and Human Services, who has been working towards improving child care in the country.